Introduction

DAY6 is a South Korean rock band under JYP Entertainment, known for their self-produced music and diverse discography. They debuted on September 7, 2015, with the EP "The Day," which peaked at No. 2 on Billboard’s World Albums Chart. The band currently consists of four members: Sungjin, Young K, Wonpil, and Dowoon, following the departures of Junhyeok in 2016 and Jae in 2022.

DAY6 gained recognition for their ambitious 2017 project, Every DAY6, where they released two songs each month, adding 25 new tracks to their discography. Their first full-length album, "Sunrise," which compiled songs from the first half of the project, was ranked No. 14 on Billboard’s 25 Greatest Kpop Albums of the 2010s, while the song "I Wait" placed No. 81 on Billboard’s 100 Greatest K-Pop Songs of the 2010s.

On August 31, 2020, DAY6 introduced their first subunit, DAY6 (Even of Day), consisting of Young K, Wonpil, and Dowoon. They debuted with the mini album "The Book of Us: Gluon – Nothing Can Tear Us Apart." Despite lineup changes, DAY6 continues to be a leading force in the Korean rock and alternative music scene.
